articles.title: Japan becomes 5th country to successfully land Lunar probe on Moon - asianews.network
articles.description: More than half a century has passed since humankind embarked on lunar exploration, and interest in the moon is once again on the rise.
articles.content:
January 22, 2024
TOKYO – A space probe launched by Japan has successfully landed on the moon, the Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA) said Saturday.
